OL,3,CPeston: Does Starmer win or lose from
OL,4,Cthe Trump rift?
OL,6,FSome of them may also say that the PM
OL,7,Fmade a mistake in alienating the most
OL,8,Fpowerful leader in the world, at a
OL,9,Ftime of international crisis, when
OL,10,Fthere was always a strong probability
OL,11,Fthat Iran would lash out at the UK and
OL,12,Fallies, such that Starmer would have
OL,13,Fto capitulate and permit the American
OL,14,Fmilitary to deploy on UK property.
OL,16,FAs a number of senior military and
OL,17,Fintelligence people have said to me,
OL,18,Fthough using slightly different words,
OL,19,Fif in this case international law was
OL,20,Fan ass, maybe the PM was too, for
OL,21,Fputting that law above realpolitik.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
